HEADWORD: Scissile
<hw>Scis"sile</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>scissilis</ets>, fr. <ets>scindere</ets>, <ets>scissum</ets>, to
cut, to split: cf. F. <ets>scissile</ets>. See <er>Schism</er>.]</ety>
<def>Capable of being cut smoothly; scissible.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
